<P>
   SCI-WATCH (Undated) _ News and notes on science: Items on bird
breeding, reducing phosphorous in chicken manure and ape origins.
By Henry Fountain. (670 words)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-KIDS-WORMS (Undated) _ A downside to modern hygiene:
Children in relatively wormfree industrialized countries have a
much greater tendency to grow up into adults with autoimmune
disorders like rheumatoid arthritis, multiple sclerosis, lupus and
inflammatory bowel disease than their third-world counterparts,
whose immune systems are constantly exposed to potential pathogens.
By Andy Newman. (1100 words)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-PATIENTS (Undated) _ Essay: Another disturbing aspect of
health care is coming up for some needed reform. The chief
executive of the King's Fund, an influential British health charity
and think tank, says it is high time to abolish the word
``patient.'' But more disturbing is the choice of what to replace
it with. By Abigail Zuger, M.D. (900 words)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-AIDS-DEATHS (Undated) _ Death rates from AIDS in the United
