</P>
<P>
   Of all the firms involved in agriculture, the largest are
already the grain traders and seed producers, most of the latter
owned by big chemical firms. &QL; 
 &LR;  &QL; 
</P>
<ANNOTATION>
    &UR; (STORY CAN END HERE AT 1,100. OPTIONAL COPY FOLLOWS TO 1,500) &LR;  &QC; 
</ANNOTATION>
 &LR;  &QL;
<P>
   Last year, Cargill, one big firm, bought the grain-trading
operations of another, Continental. For many, this exemplified the
