<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE COMMENTARY BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These columns for release Wednesday, September 1, 1999 are
moving today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ Supporters of school vouchers are reacting as if
the very idea of judicial review were novel to the point of
abomination. One supporter of a Cleveland program is calling a
judge's ruling ``an outrageous abuse of judicial power.'' It is,
instead, a perfectly ordinary, indeed predictable, finding.
(Teepen, Cox Newspapers.) MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ The world's newest political prey is the
hamburger stand, principally McDonald's and Burger King. An outlash
at McDonald's is an outlash against American foreign policy and a
deep-rooted battle in the Middle East has Burger King cringing.
(Kleinberg, Cox News Service.) MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ Whether or not I fall in love with a painting
depends strictly on how it makes me feel when I stand in front of
it. If it tries to educate me, forget it. But if the flower garden
beckons me to sit a spell on the stone bench, or if the cottage
nestled beside the stream invites me for tea in front of the fire,
I become involved. I want to crawl inside the frame and live there.
That's what happened to me this morning. (Schuett, Cox News
Service) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ When students or townfolks say that
they are deprived of their right to pray before football games,
they are providing false witness. Someone has called their hand on
a communal tradition, a hold-over from state-established religion
of yore, not on the exercising of their individual rights. Hey, if
you want a state religion, sail back to England and enjoy the
scrum. This is America. Play football. (Young, Waco Tribune-Herald)
MOVED
</P>
