<SLUG> BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HOW TO DEMYSTIFY COUSINS TANGLE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: What is a second cousin twice removed or a first cousin once
removed? I don't understand the cousin structure.
</P>
<P>
   _ N.P., Trophy Club, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: If you are not removed from a cousin, you have the same
relationship to the closest ancestor that you share.
</P>
<P>
   You have the same grandparent as your first cousin, who is a
child of your aunt or uncle.
</P>
<P>
   You have the same great-grandparent as your second cousin, the
same great-great-grandparent as your third cousin, and so on.
</P>
<P>
   A cousin who is one generation away from being your first cousin
is your first cousin once removed. The person could be either the
child of your first cousin or your parent's first cousin.
</P>
<P>
   A cousin who is two generations away from being your first
cousin is your first cousin twice removed _ either your first
cousin's grandchild or your grandparent's first cousin.
</P>
<P>
   Along these lines, a second cousin twice removed is either your
second cousin's grandchild or your grandparent's second cousin.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I write to Dwight Yoakam?
</P>
<P>
   _ B.A., Haltom City, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to him in care of the International Dwight Yoakam Fan
Club, 15030 Ventura Blvd., No. 770, Sherman Oaks, CA 91403.
</P>
<P>
   The 42-year-old singer was born in Pikeville, Ky., and grew up
in Ohio, graduating from Ohio State University.
</P>
<P>
   After seven years of trying to break into the music business,
Yoakam released ``Guitars, Cadillacs, Etc., Etc.'' in 1984 on a
small label and was signed by Reprise Records. Four songs were
added, and the revised album became his first gold record.
</P>
<P>
   In May, Yoakam released a greatest-hits collection, ``Last
Chance for a Thousand Years.'' The album includes ``Crazy Little
Thing Called Love,'' a hit song that he originally performed for a
Gap khakis commercial.
</P>
<P>
   Yoakam will star in ``The Minus Man,'' a film scheduled for
limited release in September.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I've got a 200-year calendar for 1801 to 2000 printed on a
7-by-15 piece of paper. Where can I get a new one for 2001 to 3000
or something along those lines?
</P>
<P>
   _ J.M., Grand Prairie, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Each edition of the World Almanac includes a perpetual
calendar that covers the last 20 centuries and most of the next
one.
</P>
<P>
   You can use the calendar to find out the day of the week for
birthdays and other noteworthy occasions.
</P>
<P>
   An example: In 1492, Christopher Columbus first sighted land on
Friday, Oct. 12, in the present-day Bahamas.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
