<HEADER>
A5955 &Cx1f; taf-z
u d BC-WINE-TASTING-NYT &LR;      08-31 0166
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WINE-TASTING-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WINE OF THE WEEK 
</HEADLINE>
  (jt) 
 By FRANK J. PRIAL   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; M. Trinchero Cabernet Sauvignon 1996, Napa Valley, Calif. About
$30. &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Here is a new name in the ever-expanding club of fine Napa
Valley cabernets. Well, not entirely new; the Trincheros have been
in the Napa Valley for more than half a century and own the hugely
successful Sutter Home Winery, a national leader in popular-priced
wines.
</P>
<P>
   With the market moving steadily upscale, this wine, and its
companion chardonnay, were a logical progression for the
Trincheros. It was also a good way for the present generation to
honor their late father, Mario, who left the Bronx to found Sutter
Home Winery in 1948.
</P>
<P>
   He would have been proud of this wine, a rich, full cabernet
with classic cassis aromas and beautiful structure. Fermented in
stainless steel and aged 16 months in mostly French oak, it should
improve in the bottle for five years more and last a decade after
that.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
