<P>
   N A T I O N A L/ T E X A S &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS AT LARGE-CHAPMAN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ There are two official Alamos in Texas. There is the
one that's in the heart of San Antonio, with the traffic congestion
and street noise that fill most major downtown areas. Then there is
the one in Bracketville, 150 miles away on the Southwest Texas
prairie where longhorns lie in sparse shade, rattlesnakes curl up
under rocks, and cactuses spring from hard-pan soil. It is quiet
there. The way it should be at a Spanish mission. Also, it was
there that John Wayne, dressed like Davy Crockett, whopped the
advancing troops of Antonio Lopez de Santa Anna over the head with
the butt of his muzzleloader. No wonder people get the authenticity
of the two Alamos confused. By ART CHAPMAN. Story has moved in
``a'' general news category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   E N T E R T A I N M E N T &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DIXIE CHICKS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Not long ago, the Dixie Chicks were likely to be seen
at a Dallas bar or wedding near you. But now, after selling 6
