   WALLST _ Y2K arrived on Wall Street in August, when debt markets
were flooded with third quarter offerings by companies unwilling to
chance a year-end computer glitch. On Main Street, however, the
much ballyhooed prospect that computers might fail on Jan. 1, 2000,
apparently is being viewed by individual investors as a yawner.
(Walker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
