million in venture capital in the last few weeks and has grown from
five employees to 55 since it was founded. (Clothier, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   MVP _ ATLANTA _ Pro football great John Elway partners with
Altanta firm to develop new Web site focusing on sports and fitness
for men 35 and older. The Atlanta firm had originally suggested
Elway be a spokesman for an online brokerage firm they were
developing, but Elway decided to take the v venture in a different
direction. Site is expected to launch during the superbowl here in
ATL in January 2000. (Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   WORLDACCESS _ATLANTA _ World Access, interview with the CEO of
an Atlanta company that has quietly grown to $1.2 billion, becoming
in the process one of the leaders in European long-distance. How
come nobody knows this guy? (Kanell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
