number of fatal crashes hit a 42-year low last year and the decline
is continuing this year, according to CHP statistics. Also on the
decline are motorcycle and pedestrian fatalities. Officials
attribute the state-wide decline to safer cars, better life-saving
techniques and more drivers complying with safety rules. By Lisa
Van Proyen. (Will move in the ``n'' California news file.)
