<TEXT>
<P>
   VIDEO: ``FAMOUS FRED''
</P>
<P>
   Starring: Lenny Henry as the voice of Fred, Tom Courtney as the
voice of Kenneth and David Robb as the voice of Ginger.
</P>
<P>
   Plot: A sassy cat named Fred dies and his owners discover the
secret of Fred's nightlife: He was really a famous singer. In fact,
his style was a lot like Elvis'! Fred was adored by all the cats in
the world before he died of the flu. But don't worry, feline
friends, Fred comes back to life because he has only used up eight
of his nine lives.
</P>
<P>
   Comments: This movie was entertaining and would be appealing to
students in elementary school. The story was based on a book by
Posy Simmonds. The video was a 1997 Academy Awards nominee for Best
Animated Short Film.
