<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-31 20:18 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A6367 &Cx1f; tab-z
r l BC-KIDS:FACES:ASHLEY-CAN     08-31 0488
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-KIDS:FACES:ASHLEY-CANTLEY-CLASSACTS-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FACES: MEET ASHLEY CANTLEY, FINALIST IN CHANEL/``SEVENTEEN'' MODEL
CONTEST 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 By JESSAMY BROWN 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Meet: Ashley Cantley.
</P>
<P>
   Age: 16.
</P>
<P>
   Hometown: Mesquite, Texas.
</P>
<P>
   Claim to fame: Finalist in the Chanel/``Seventeen'' New Model of
the Year Contest.
</P>
<P>
   Hobbies: Photography.
</P>
<P>
   Pets: A dog, two cats, two Australian flying squirrels, three
salamanders and a school of fish.
</P>
<P>
   If you didn't know Ashley Cantley, you might think her life as a
teen model is easy.
</P>
<P>
   After all, her break into the modeling world began with just a
routine trip to the mall when she was 13. A talent scout from Page
Parkes Model's Rep in Dallas spotted her shopping and persuaded her
to give the business a try. Ashley eventually signed with The
Campbell Agency in Dallas and began appearing in catalogs for
department stores J.C. Penney and Dillard's.
</P>
<P>
   This summer, the junior got another big break. Competing against
20,000 girls ages 14 to 20, she was selected as one of eight
finalists in the Chanel/``Seventeen'' New Model of the Year
Contest. In May, Ashley flew to New York City for hair and make-up
sessions, a photo shoot and a runway show attended by the press at
the Chanel Boutique.
</P>
<P>
   But Ashley will tell you that what she does requires a lot of
effort. ``My friends don't believe me when I tell them it's hard
work,'' she says. ``It's really tiring. When I get home from
shooting all day I'm tired. It may be because of the pressure, when
the photographer wants a certain look or mood you have to show it.
It's like acting to a still camera.''
</P>
<P>
   To boost her stamina and to stay fit, Ashley, who describes
herself as ``totally not athletic,'' recently took up running. She
picked the hottest time of the year to begin; with Texas
temperatures reaching above 100 degrees, Ashley has to wait until 9
p.m. or later to hit the streets.
</P>
<P>
   An honor student and student government participant, Ashley
tries to keep a balance between her career and her everyday life.
</P>
<P>
   ``Today I went to school with mascara on but no other makeup,''
she says. ``I know it's impossible to look like I do in photos.
Sometimes, they don't even look anything like me.''
</P>
<P>
   But what about the future? Will she stay with modeling?
</P>
<P>
   ``It would be nice,'' she says. ``There are millions of girls
trying to do the same thing. I've wanted to be a pediatrician for a
long time, but 10 more years of school? I'm not sure.''
</P>
<P>
   She has a while to decide. Meanwhile, check Ashley out in the
Chanel special advertising section in the September issue of
``Seventeen.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
