<P>
   INSURANCE (Seattle) _ Regence Blue Shield will stop selling
health insurance to individuals and families, leaving only Group
Health as a major insurer offering private plans in King, Pierce
and Snohomish counties. In fact, 25 counties in Washington state
will have no private insurance plans available for individuals or
families and 11 other counties will have only one option. Insurers
blame the rising costs of providing these plans since they're no
longer allowed to exclude pre-existing conditions.
</P>
<P>
   By Bruce Ramsey. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
