Village, features raw tuna, scallops in coconut milk, squid in an
herb dressing and oysters with onion and chilies. Ceviche has
expanded the world of flavors and textures created in fish when no
cooking is involved. (Boyd Hagen/New York Times Photo) LITE
</P>
