<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR WEDNESDAY, SEPTEMBER 1
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-AT&AMP;T-RATES-NYT (moved on Monday, Aug. 30)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, Aug. 30,
about a new long-distance rate plan offered by AT&AMP;T misstated the
terms of a competing plan from MCI Worldcom. The MCI plan that
offers evening and weekend calls for 5 cents a minute and weekday
calls for 10 cents a minute has a monthly fee of $4.95, not $5.95.
</P>
<P>
   BC-TEACHER-SHORTAGE-NYT (moved on Monday, Aug. 30)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, Aug. 30,
about teacher shortages in the United States referred imprecisely
to the place where cash bonuses of up to $3,000 each are being
offered to prospective teachers. It is Washington, D.C., not
Washington State.
</P>
<P>
   BC-SCI-AIDS-DEATHS-NYT (moved on Monday, Aug. 30)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, Aug. 30,
about a slowing in the decline of H.I.V. infection and AIDS
misstated the results of a study by the Centers for Disease Control
and Prevention on new infections among people treated in clinics
specializing in sexually transmitted disease. The rates were 8
percent among gay and bisexual men and 0.48 percent among
heterosexuals, not 6 percent and 0.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
   BC-NEWSPAPER-CLASSIFIED-MEDIA-NYT (moved on Sunday, Aug. 29)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Aug. 29,
about the Drudge Report's on-line disclosure of part of a
preliminary article list circulated within the New York Times
newsroom misidentified the Times division that distributes such
lists to newspaper clients. It is The New York Times News Service,
not The New York Times Syndicate.
</P>
</TEXT>
